PORTO RICO FERTILIZER COMPANY, Plaintiff, Appellant, v. Pedro GANDIA, Defendant, Appellee. (Circuit Court of Appeals, First Circuit. October 23, 1925.) No. 1876. Cayetano Coll y Cuchi, of San Juan, Porto Rico, for appellant. Jose A. Poventud, of New York City, for appellee.

Before BINGHAM, JOHNSON, and ANDERSON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment of the Supreme Court of Porto Rico, March 19, 1925, conforms to the mandate of this court of February 14, 1025, and the order is: Judgment affirmed, with, costs to the appellee. See, also, 2 F. (2d) 611.
